  "text": "GCC generates DWARF debug information through a well-structured pipeline that connects language front-ends to the DWARF output generator. Here is the complete tracing of the flow:\n\n## 1. Debug Hooks Interface (gcc/debug.h:28)\n\nThe `gcc_debug_hooks` structure in gcc/debug.h defines the plugin interface that language front-ends use to communicate debug information to the backend. This structure contains function pointers for various debug events, including:\n- `init()` - Initialize debug output\n- `finish()` - Output final debug symbols\n- `early_global_decl()` - Process declarations early\n- `late_global_decl()` - Process declarations after optimization\n- `function_decl()` - Process function declarations\n- `type_decl()` - Process type declarations\n- `source_line()` - Record source line locations\n- `var_location()` - Record variable locations\n\n## 2. DWARF Debug Hooks Implementation (gcc/dwarf2out.cc:2893)\n\nThe `dwarf2_debug_hooks` structure in gcc/dwarf2out.cc:2893 is the DWARF-specific implementation of the debug hooks interface. It routes all debug events through DWARF-specific handler functions like:\n- `dwarf2out_early_global_decl()` - Early processing of global declarations\n- `dwarf2out_late_global_decl()` - Late processing after optimization\n- `dwarf2out_function_decl()` - Function-specific processing\n- `dwarf2out_type_decl()` - Type-specific processing\n- `dwarf2out_source_line()` - Source line recording\n- `dwarf2out_var_location()` - Variable location tracking\n\n## 3. DWARF DIE (Debug Info Entry) Structure (gcc/dwarf2out.cc:3146)\n\nThe `die_struct` (typedef'd as `die_node`) in gcc/dwarf2out.cc:3146 is the core data structure representing a DWARF Debugging Information Entry. It includes:\n- `die_tag` - The DWARF tag type (DW_TAG_subprogram, DW_TAG_variable, etc.)\n- `die_attr` - Vector of attribute/value pairs\n- `die_parent` - Reference to parent DIE\n- `die_child` - Reference to first child DIE\n- `die_sib` - Reference to sibling DIE (forms circular list)\n- `die_offset` - Offset in the .debug_info section\n- `die_abbrev` - Abbreviation number\n\n## 4. DIE Creation Functions (gcc/dwarf2out.cc:5850-5900)\n\nTwo key functions create DIEs:\n\n**new_die_raw()** (gcc/dwarf2out.cc:5850-5855):\n- Allocates a new DIE structure using ggc_cleared_alloc\n- Sets the DWARF tag\n- Returns the newly created DIE reference\n\n**new_die()** (gcc/dwarf2out.cc:5863-5900):\n- Calls new_die_raw() to create the DIE\n- If parent_die is provided, adds the DIE as a child using add_child_die()\n- If parent_die is NULL, places the DIE in \"limbo\" for later processing\n- Handles special cases for nested functions and COMDAT types\n\n## 5. Location Descriptor Creation (gcc/dwarf2out.cc:1413-1428)\n\nThe `new_loc_descr()` function creates location descriptors that describe variable locations in the code. It:\n- Allocates a dw_loc_descr_node structure\n- Sets the DWARF location operation code (DW_OP_*)\n- Initializes operands with unsigned integer values\n- Returns a reference to the location descriptor\n\nThese location descriptors are chained together to form complex location expressions.\n\n## 6. Attribute Addition (gcc/dwarf2out.cc:4493-4515)\n\nThe `add_dwarf_attr()` function adds attributes to DIEs. It:\n- Takes a DIE reference and an attribute node\n- Reserves space in the DIE's attribute vector\n- Pushes the new attribute onto the vector\n- Performs duplicate checking in debug builds\n\nMultiple add_AT_* functions (like add_AT_int, add_AT_string, add_AT_loc) create specific attribute types before passing them to add_dwarf_attr().\n\n## 7. Line Number Table Emission (gcc/dwarf2out.cc:13137)\n\nThe `output_line_info()` function in gcc/dwarf2out.cc:13137-13129 generates the .debug_line section:\n- Outputs the DWARF line table header with version, minimum instruction length, and line base/range\n- Iterates through line information entries (dw_line_info_entry)\n- Emits DWARF line number state machine instructions:\n  - DW_LNE_set_address - Set the current address\n  - DW_LNS_advance_line - Change the current line number\n  - DW_LNS_set_file - Set the current file\n  - DW_LNS_copy - Emit a line table row\n  - DW_LNE_set_discriminator - Set discriminator for duplicate lines\n- Outputs the end sequence marker\n\n## Complete Information Flow\n\n1. **Front-end calls debug hooks** - Language front-ends invoke hooks from gcc_debug_hooks when processing declarations and source lines\n2. **DWARF handlers process events** - dwarf2out_*.* functions receive the calls and convert them to DWARF-specific operations\n3. **DIEs are created** - new_die() creates DIE nodes representing types, functions, variables, etc.\n4. **Attributes are added** - add_dwarf_attr() and add_AT_* functions add detailed information to DIEs\n5. **Location information is recorded** - new_loc_descr() creates location expressions for variables\n6. **DIE trees are built** - add_child_die() establishes parent-child relationships between DIEs, forming the DWARF tree\n7. **Line information is tracked** - Source line locations are recorded in dw_line_info_table structures\n8. **Output is emitted** - During final code generation, dwarf2out_finish() traverses the DIE tree and output_line_info() emits the .debug_line section\n\nThe key supporting files are:\n- **gcc/debug.h** - Debug hooks interface definition\n- **gcc/debug.cc** - Default no-op implementation of debug hooks\n- **gcc/dwarf2out.h** - DWARF-specific data structures and public interfaces\n- **gcc/dwarf2out.cc** - Complete DWARF generation implementation (19000+ lines)\n- **gcc/dwarf2asm.cc** - DWARF assembly output generation utilities\n- **gcc/dwarf2cfi.cc** - Call Frame Information (CFI) generation"
